Package: PowerCHORD
Type: Package
Title: Power Analysis and Cosinor design optimization for HOmoscedastic Rhythm Detection  (PowerCHORD)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
  c(person('Silverthorne','Turner',email='turner.silverthorne@gmail.com',role=c('cre','aut')),
    person('Carlucci','Matthew',role='ctb'),
    person('Stinchcombe','Adam',role='ctb'))
Maintainer: Turner Silverthorne <turner.silverthorne@gmail.com>
Description:  PowerCHORD is an open source package for maximizing the statistical power of biological rhythm detection studies. It includes R functions for evaluating the exact power of cosinor-based hypothesis tests. PowerCHORD also provides access to low-level optimization methods to construct designs of maximal statistical power.
